   "source": [
    "1. What is a parameter?\n",
    "A value inside a model that the algorithm learns from data (like weights in linear regression).\n",
    "\n",
    "2. What is correlation?\n",
    "A measure of how strongly two variables move together.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. What does negative correlation mean?\n",
    "When one variable increases, the other decreases.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. Define Machine Learning. What are the main components in Machine Learning?\n",
    "ML is teaching machines to learn patterns from data.\n",
    "Components: data, model, algorithm, training, testing.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. How does loss value help in determining whether the model is good or not?\n",
    "Lower loss = better model; it shows how far predictions are from actual values.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. What are continuous and categorical variables?\n",
    "Continuous: Numeric values (like height, age).\n",
    "Categorical: Categories (like gender, color).\n",
    "\n",
    "7. How do we handle categorical variables in Machine Learning? What are the common techniques?\n",
    "Using encoding:\n",
    "\n",
    "One-Hot Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "Label Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "Ordinal Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "8. What do you mean by training and testing a dataset?\n",
    "\n",
    "Training: Teach the model.\n",
    "\n",
    "Testing: Check if the model learned well.\n",
    "\n",
    "9. What is sklearn.preprocessing?\n",
    "A module in Scikit-learn to prepare (scale/encode/transform) data for ML models.\n",
    "\n",
    "10. What is a Test set?\n",
    "The data used to evaluate model performance after training.\n",
    "\n",
    "11. How do we split data for model fitting (training and testing) in Python?\n",
    "Using train_test_split() from sklearn.model_selection.\n",
    "\n",
    "12. How do you approach a Machine Learning problem?\n",
    "\n",
    "Understand the problem\n",
    "\n",
    "Collect & clean data\n",
    "\n",
    "EDA\n",
    "\n",
    "Encode & scale\n",
    "\n",
    "Train model\n",
    "\n",
    "Evaluate\n",
    "\n",
    "Improve\n",
    "\n",
    "13. Why do we have to perform EDA before fitting a model to the data?\n",
    "To understand data patterns, detect errors, outliers, and relationships.\n",
    "\n",
    "14. What is correlation?\n",
    "Already answered in #2.\n",
    "\n",
    "15. What does negative correlation mean?\n",
    "Already answered in #3.\n",
    "\n",
    "16. How can you find correlation between variables in Python?\n",
    "Use .corr() in pandas and visualize with a heatmap using seaborn.\n",
    "\n",
    "17. What is causation? Explain difference between correlation and causation with an example.\n",
    "Causation: A causes B.\n",
    "Correlation: A and B move together, but A may not cause B.\n",
    "Example: Ice cream sales and drowning are correlated, but both are caused by summer.\n",
    "\n",
    "18. What is an Optimizer? What are different types of optimizers? Explain each with an example.\n",
    "Optimizer improves model by reducing loss.\n",
    "Types:\n",
    "SGD: Basic gradient steps.\n",
    "Adam: Adaptive steps (faster).\n",
    "RMSprop: Works well with RNNs.\n",
    "Example in TensorFlow: optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam()\n",
    "\n",
    "19. What is sklearn.linear_model?\n",
    "A module in Scikit-learn that has linear models like LinearRegression, LogisticRegression.\n",
    "\n",
    "20. What does model.fit() do? What arguments must be given?\n",
    "Trains the model on training data.\n",
    "Arguments: features (X), target (y).\n",
    "\n",
    "21. What does model.predict() do? What arguments must be given?\n",
    "Makes predictions on new/unseen data.\n",
    "Argument: features (X_test).\n",
    "\n",
